question: The "Elling Woman" and "Tollund Man" are the mummified corpses discovered and preserved in which country?
explanation: The "Elling Woman" and "Tollund Man" are the mummified corpses discovered and preserved in Denmark. Tollund Man was lived during the 4th century B.C. in the Pre-Roman Iron Age of Scandinavia. This mummy was discovered in 1950. Elling Woman was discovered in 1938. Both are preserved and displayed at Silkeborg Museum in Denmark.
